Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "smešan" in different forms and positions:

1. *Smešan* je ovaj vic. (This joke is *funny*.)
2. Nisam siguran da li je situacija *smešna* ili tužna. (I'm not sure if the situation is *amusing* or sad.)
3. Zbog njegovog *smešnog* ponašanja, niko ga ne shvata ozbiljno. (Because of his *ridiculous* behavior, nobody takes him seriously.)
4. On je glumac koji je poznat po svojim *smešnim* ulogama. (He's an actor known for his *comic* roles.)
5. Nije u redu da se *smeješ* tuđim nevoljama. (It's not right to *laugh* at other people's misfortunes.)
6. Moja sestra je jako *smešna* osoba. (My sister is a very *humorous* person.)
7. *Smejao* se do suza dok je gledao taj film. (He *laughed* so hard that he cried while watching that movie.)
8. Zbog njenog *smejanja* celi bioskop je počeo da se smeje. (Because of her *laughter*, the whole movie theater started laughing.)

I hope these examples help!